Starting from the Shell
-----------------------

    ASX can be started from the shell by typing its name and the
parameters you need.  Enter @{b}ASX ?@{ub} for a shell usage template.

    The @{b}ENV:asx.prefs@{ub} configuration file will be loaded and processed
immediately, if not otherwise desired (see the @{b}LOCALPREFS@{ub} argument
below).  The configuration file is an ASCII text that can be edited
using a texteditor if needed.

    If ASX is already running and you invoke it again, it will open the
user interface window of the already running version.

    There is no need to use the AmigaDOS @{b}Run@{ub} command to start ASX as it
will automatically self-detach from the shell or CLI that it was
started from.

